5:
"This Just In! Bodies Rising from the
Grave!"
For real? Headlines these days, I
swear...
10:
Haven't you heard, Alk? There's been
a ton of reports about the dead
coming back to life! No one knows
what's going on!
15:
Wait, this wasn't a joke post? Huh...
Sounds like we've got a
necromancer problem on our hands.
19:
Honestly? No one's sure. Seems like
the bodies stop moving and go
back to normal after a day. Does
that sound like a necromancer to
you?
21:
What if it's a new disease? Or the
magic of an evil cult? Gives me
shivers just thinking about it!
25:
Anyway, let me know if you find out
anything! There could be a reward
in it for you!
29:
Temporary zombies... What—or
who—could be causing that?
37:
M-mercy, please! I swear, no more
dragging pretty ladies down a
sketchy alley ever again! I'll be
good! Cross my heart and hope to
die!
39:
Blah, blah, blah. Whatever, man.
You're making way too much of a
fuss, y'know that? Just shut up and
die.
46:
Hold it right there! I know not what
this man has done to you, but if you
strike him again he will surely die!
50:
Huh? Who the hell are you?
Also, don't be stupid. I can't bring
him back to life if he's not dead first.
60:
Gah! My perfectly fine specimen!
Look what you did!
63:
Sheeeesh! Can't a girl get a break?
None of my revival concoctions
work like they're supposed to, then
when I try to get a fresh body, this
happens!
66:
Aaaahhhhhh! I'm so mad, I just
wanna slice something up into
PIECES!
76:
Why did you DODGE?! You... REALLY!
PISS! ME! OFF! RAAAAHHH!
80:
AHHH! Runaway horse cart!
Everybody, steer clear!
83:
Jeez, I felt that brush my fur... What
kinda horse comes barreling down
an alley—
86:
AHHH! A golem from the academy is
on the loose! And... monsters from
the Kaleidoscope too!
89:
Does this alley have a magnet for 
attracting trouble or something? 
The hell!
92:
Guess we better settle this before
anything else happens. Come at me!
109:
Oh my gosh, oh my GOSH! The way
you whisked me away and
pummeled that golem... Talk about
dashing! Ugh, stop wasting time
and marry me already!
114:
Uh... Think I might've heard you
wrong. What'd... you just say?
120:
I like you, you big furball! Now
gimme a kiss!
125:
The hell are you on about? Did you
hit your head back there?!
131:
Don't you like me back, baby? Am I
not your type? Give me a chance
and I'll become the woman of your
dreams!
136:
This chick is off her damn rocker...
Listen, the problem here has nothin'
to do with type or whatever.
140:
I'm a beastman. A furless lady just
ain't gonna cut it for me. Fact is...
only the shiniest coats out there'll
catch my attention.
147: Wait, what? Last time I checked, you—
152:
SHH! Can't you tell I'm making this
crap up?!
155:
Anyway, there you have it. Quit while
you're ahead.
167: The hell is wrong with her...
173:
So the reports about corpses
coming back to life have stopped?
178:
Yep, not a single dead person
spotted stumbling around! I wonder
what all the fuss was originally
about...
183:
Forget that crap! Someone get this
woman off of me!
188:
Nimbus! I'll never give up on you, my
love!
194:
I'd rather you did, thanks! Like I said,
if you're not covered in fur—
199:
That's why I started developing a
concoction to give me the most
beautiful coat there ever was!
207:
Oh yes, I'm quite the potion expert.
Just give me some time! I'll become
the furriest furball you've ever laid
eyes on!
212:
Hold up, how do you even know
Nimbus's name?
217:
I looked into it, duh. You adventuring
types are super easy to track!
Knowing names is useful since we're
gonna be future travel buddies!
233:
Name's Sohvi. It's good meet ya,
Stella. Alk. Light.
238: You even figured out our names?!
243:
Nimbus... I'll make you fall for me, no
matter what...
